Description: The Clarity program introduces for the first time in Greece the obligation to publish all the decisions on the Internet- with the exception of decisions that contain sensitive personal data and/or information on national security. It is quite an innovative program- even by European standards- aiming first of all to bring about the maximum publicity of the government policy and administrative action. The use of Internet guarantees wide publicity and access to information- progressively contributing to a culture change in the whole of the Public Administration.
